{
  "texts": [
    "We assess the ability of learned representations to predict protein stability using the database of melting temperatures reported in the FLIP set of benchmarks 43.",
    "This dataset was constructed from a collection of proteome-wide denaturation experiments reported in the Meltome Atlas 55.",
    "Measured melting temperatures range between 30 and 90 °C, with most of the support in the range between 30 and 55 °C.",
    "We used the same splits and homology removal protocol as in FLIP 43, where data was clustered at 20% sequence identity.",
    "Subcellular localization."
  ]
}